						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the southern gate of jamā masjid.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Top portion of the slab is broken and lost. It refers to a tax free gift (of land) situated in Poṭṭaḷakeṟe to the god (name lost) for <hi rend="italic">dēvabōga.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
